commit.message: Bumping version to 0.1.26
Changing the locate functions so that they work with unicode types on Python 2.
Added some comments and docstring. Updated setup.py to Python 3.8 now that Pillow supports 3.8.
Added a stress test.

Made Pillow a hard requirement for the general unit test. Got rid of test_pillowNotPresent() because this is done by test_pillow_unavailable.py now, and the sys.modules['PIL'] = None technique is no longer allowed by Python. (It causes a "ModuleNotFoundError: import of PIL halted; None in sys.modules" error.)

Moved the "from contextlib import contextmanager" line up a bit.

Modified PyScreeze so that Pillow isn't a hard requirement for PyScreeze to be installed, but the Pillow-dependent functions will raise a PyScreezeException when called if Pillow isn't installed.

I made this change because PyAutoGUI will try to install PyScreeze, and this shouldn't fail just because Pillow isn't available. (I'm doing something similar with the MouseInfo package for the same reason.)

test_pillow_unavailable.py ensures the exceptions are raised.

Added a requiresPillow decorator for any Pillow-dependent functions.

Added TODO comments for all docstrings.

Moved all the import statements to the top of the file.

Changed setup.py so that PyScreeze install will complete even if Pillow doesn't support the current Python version.
Ran Black over setup.py
Added more comments to setup.py
Refactoring setup.py.
Fixed monitor DPI scaling issue on Windows.
Updated tests to consider the USE_IMAGE_NOT_FOUND_EXCEPTION constant.
Added -z option to scrot to silence the beep.

Bumping version to 0.1.21. Fix memory leak at pixel(). Fix to pixel function. Fix cropped image saving on Linux and Mac. Fix UnboundLocalError (img_cv won't be assigned) when img is a true-color array.
Merge branch 'ijknabla-debug'
Merge branch 'debug' of https://github.com/ijknabla/pyscreeze into ijknabla-debug

commit.message: Renamed tests, adjusted tests now that not finding an image raises an exception instead of returning None.
Adding a Point and RGB namedtuple. These are backwards compatible with the previous usage.
Getting rid of RAISE_IF_NOT_FOUND and just always raising ImageNotFoundException if images can't be found. Returning Box namedtuples instead of regular (left, top, width, height) tuples.
Getting rid of the leading . in macOS filenames because in Mojave this causes errors. See https://github.com/asweigart/pyautogui/issues/269
Updating .gitignore file.

fix cropped image saving on Linux and Mac

As referenced in pyautogui's issue 286 (https://github.com/asweigart/pyautogui/issues/286), currently a call to the screenshot function that includes both a region and filename will save an image of the entire screen to the filesystem, but return a cropped image. 
This change would make the image saved on the filesystem (for osx and linux) also be the cropped version, which is what the user would expect, and mirrors the behavior on win32.

fix cropped image saving on Linux and Mac

As referenced in pyautogui's issue 286 (https://github.com/asweigart/pyautogui/issues/286), currently a call to the screenshot function that includes both a region and filename will save an image of the entire screen to the filesystem, but return a cropped image. 
This change would make the image saved on the filesystem (for osx and linux) also be the cropped version, which is what the user would expect, and mirrors the behavior on win32.
